                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14476293" author="melix" created="Mon, 28 Jul 2014 02:15:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that the example doesn&apos;t really make sense: a placeholder at the method level is supposed to be used in the method signature itself. Here, it&apos;s neither used in the return type nor the parameters. This means that it&apos;s useless, as the compiler cannot infer its type.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14476343" author="tachatte" created="Mon, 28 Jul 2014 02:18:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi C&#195;&#169;dric,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;it is the simplest example I came with. My use case was more complex than that, something like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;A {
   void bar(Callable&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; callable) { ... }
   &amp;lt;R&amp;gt; void foo() {
      bar(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Callable&amp;lt;R&amp;gt;() {
         R call() {
            ...
         }
      }
   }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14476330" author="melix" created="Mon, 28 Jul 2014 02:23:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, this time this remembers me of another bug. I&apos;m pretty sure it&apos;s a duplicate, I&apos;ll try to find it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
